The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Monday, December 13, 2004 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Dec. 12: Four extortionists were beaten to death today at Deula station in Usthi, South 24-Parganas, about 65 km from here. 

 Police said four armed men were collecting money at gunpoint from vegetable sellers at the station when passengers gave them a chase and caught them. Three of the goons died on the spot.

 Krishnagar: Thirteen-year-old Durga Pal told police on Sunday that her mother was driven to suicide by her father, uncle and aunt. Sobha Pal, who set herself ablaze on Saturday, died at Shaktinagar District Hospital here on Sunday. Durga?s father Makhan, uncle Ranjit and aunt Jyotsna were arrested from Dhubulia in Nadia, about 120 km from Calcutta, after she lodged an FIR. The girl said in the complaint that her mother was tortured relentlessly for money.

 Calcutta: There was smoke at Writers? Buildings on Sunday afternoon when a transformer on the ground floor caught fire. No one was hurt and nothing was damaged. Police said two fire engines controlled it.

 Burdwan: The district police on Sunday suspended assistant sub-inspector Dibakar Mondal and constable Subhas Ghosh on charges of dereliction of duty after an undertrial allegedly committed suicide by hanging on Saturday night in the lockup of Purbasthali police station, 80 km from Calcutta. The authorities also replaced Tapan Chowbey, officer-in-charge of the police station with sub-inspector Saikat Roy.




